Step 1 :    create the virtual environment

    virtualenv <proj-name>
    
 Step 2 :    cd to the proj dicrectory and type:
 
     source bin/activate
       
 Step 3 :     Install the packages inside the folder proj ( virtualenv ) 
 
      pip3 install psycopg2-binary
      pip3 install sqlalchemy
      pip3 install flask
      
Step 4 :    Build a flask aplication

--------------------
app.py sample
--------------------

from flask import Flask, render_template

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route("/")
def show_projects():
    return render_template("index.html")

app.run(debug=True, host="127.0.0.1", port=3000)


  run:
  
  python3 app.py
  
 


---------------------
Step 5 :  Create another directory 

      templates - So the router function can access it 

